   pressure, as increasing wildebeest (Connochaetes taurinus) numbers have
   reduced the volume of combustible material present, and hence the
   frequency of damaging `hot burns'. We conclude that this globally
   threatened warbler appears to have benefited from changes in ungulate
   populations in the Serengeti, which have influenced burning intensity
   and hence tree regeneration. The warbler's range now appears to be
