Pages = {{2571-2577}},
Abstract = {{The distribution of predatory soil nematodes (Mononchida) across Europe
   is well described. However, in Ireland knowledge of mononchids is
   limited to a single study. The CreBeo project was the first systematic
   survey of soil biodiversity in the major land-use types across the
   Republic of Ireland. Nematodes were sampled from 61 locations with an
   extensive geographical spread including arable, pasture, broadleaf
   forest, coniferous plantation, rough grazing and peatland sites. This
   study resulted in 11 first records of mononchid species from Ireland (of
   which 2 are new records for Britain and Ireland). We discuss the
